{"title_page": "New Port South", "text_new": "{{short description|2001 film by Kyle Cooper}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = New Port South\n| image = New port south.jpg\n| caption = DVD cover\n| director = [[Kyle Cooper]]\n| producer = [[John Hughes (filmmaker)|John Hughes]]\n| writer = James Hughes\n| starring = [[Todd Field]]<br>[[Will Estes]]<br>[[Blake Shields]]\n| music = [[Telefon Tel Aviv]]\n| cinematography = [[Juan Ruiz Anch\u00eda]]\n| editing = Lawrence Jordan\n| studio = [[Touchstone Pictures]]<br>[[John Hughes (filmmaker)|Hughes Entertainment]]\n| distributor  = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Buena Vista Pictures]]\n| released = {{Film date|2001|09|07}}\n| runtime = 95 minutes\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n}}\n\n'''''New Port South''''' is a 2001 [[drama film]]. The film is set in the fictional town of New Port, near [[Chicago]]. It stars [[Will Estes]], [[Todd Field]], and [[Blake Shields]], was written by James Hughes and directed by [[Kyle Cooper]]. The soundtrack is by [[Telefon Tel Aviv]].<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0229003/ New Port South (2001)]. IMDB. Accessed April 5, 2012.</ref>\n\nJames Hughes is the son of [[John Hughes (filmmaker)|John Hughes]], who produced the movie (one of only two in his career that he produced without writing himself - the other was ''[[Only the Lonely (film)|Only the Lonely]]'').{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}\n\n==Plot==\nWill Maddox ([[Blake Shields]]) has a theory about students not liking the idea of school and authority and thinking that it is a prison. He tests this theory and examines the boundaries of authority and his friendships. A few years before, a student, John Stanton ([[Michael Shannon]]) was committed to an insane asylum, for reasons unknown to most everybody except the principal. One day he escapes, releasing everyone else from the [[Psychiatric hospital|asylums]] around. Maddox sees this defiance which is the start of his anarchy. Maddox wants to \"help him\" and understand him more so they start a correspondence and Stanton tells him what to do and how to do it. This is includes the erasing of student grades, posting posters/fliers, and locking part of the student body in a room, among other things. Maddox gets his friends involved and challenges authority and gets most of the school behind him, including an administrator for a while. He is so consumed with creating chaos and disorder that his friends start to see the destruction, but they have to save themselves, and him before he can take complete control over the school.<ref>[https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/252769/New-Port-South/overview New Port South - The New York Times]. Accessed April 5, 2012.</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Todd Field]] as Mr. Walsh\n* [[Will Estes]] as Chris\n* [[Blake Shields]] as Will Maddox\n* Kevin Christy as Clip\n* [[Melissa George]] as Amanda\n* [[Raymond J. Barry]] as Edwards\n* [[Gabriel Mann (actor)|Gabriel Mann]] as Michael \"Mike\" Wilson\n* Brad Eric Johnson as Knox\n* Lamar Benson as Football Player\n* Nick Sandow as Armstrong\n* [[Michael Shannon]] as John Stanton\n\n==Filming locations==\n* [[Libertyville High School]], [[Libertyville, Illinois|Libertyville]], [[Illinois]] (and the city of Libertyville itself).\n* [[Lake Bluff]], [[Illinois]]\n\n==Home media==\nA region 1 DVD of the film was released on March 12, 2002.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0229003|title=New Port South}}\n* {{Mojo title|newportsouth}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|new_port_south}}\n\n[[Category:2001 films]]\n[[Category:2000s drama films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Touchstone Pictures films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Films produced by John Hughes (filmmaker)]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2001 film by Kyle Cooper}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = New Port South\n| image = New port south.jpg\n| caption = DVD cover\n| director = [[Kyle Cooper]]\n| producer = [[John Hughes (filmmaker)|John Hughes]]\n| writer = James Hughes\n| starring = [[Todd Field]]<br>[[Will Estes]]<br>[[Blake Shields]]\n| music = [[Telefon Tel Aviv]]\n| cinematography = [[Juan Ruiz Anch\u00eda]]\n| studio = [[Touchstone Pictures]]<br>[[John Hughes (filmmaker)|Hughes Entertainment]]\n| distributor  = [[Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures|Buena Vista Pictures]]\n| released = {{Film date|2001|09|07}}\n| runtime = 95 minutes\n| country = United States\n| language = English\n}}\n\n'''''New Port South''''' is a 2001 [[drama film]]. The film is set in the fictional town of New Port, near [[Chicago]]. It stars [[Will Estes]], [[Todd Field]], and [[Blake Shields]], was written by James Hughes and directed by [[Kyle Cooper]]. The soundtrack is by [[Telefon Tel Aviv]].<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0229003/ New Port South (2001)]. IMDB. Accessed April 5, 2012.</ref>\n\nJames Hughes is the son of [[John Hughes (filmmaker)|John Hughes]], who produced the movie (one of only two in his career that he produced without writing himself - the other was ''[[Only the Lonely (film)|Only the Lonely]]'').{{citation needed|date=April 2013}}\n\n==Plot==\nWill Maddox ([[Blake Shields]]) has a theory about students not liking the idea of school and authority and thinking that it is a prison. He tests this theory and examines the boundaries of authority and his friendships. A few years before, a student, John Stanton ([[Michael Shannon]]) was committed to an insane asylum, for reasons unknown to most everybody except the principal. One day he escapes, releasing everyone else from the [[Psychiatric hospital|asylums]] around. Maddox sees this defiance which is the start of his anarchy. Maddox wants to \"help him\" and understand him more so they start a correspondence and Stanton tells him what to do and how to do it. This is includes the erasing of student grades, posting posters/fliers, and locking part of the student body in a room, among other things. Maddox gets his friends involved and challenges authority and gets most of the school behind him, including an administrator for a while. He is so consumed with creating chaos and disorder that his friends start to see the destruction, but they have to save themselves, and him before he can take complete control over the school.<ref>[https://movies.nytimes.com/movie/252769/New-Port-South/overview New Port South - The New York Times]. Accessed April 5, 2012.</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Todd Field]] as Mr. Walsh\n* [[Will Estes]] as Chris\n* [[Blake Shields]] as Will Maddox\n* Kevin Christy as Clip\n* [[Melissa George]] as Amanda\n* [[Raymond J. Barry]] as Edwards\n* [[Gabriel Mann (actor)|Gabriel Mann]] as Michael \"Mike\" Wilson\n* Brad Eric Johnson as Knox\n* Lamar Benson as Football Player\n* Nick Sandow as Armstrong\n* [[Michael Shannon]] as John Stanton\n\n==Filming locations==\n* [[Libertyville High School]], [[Libertyville, Illinois|Libertyville]], [[Illinois]] (and the city of Libertyville itself).\n* [[Lake Bluff]], [[Illinois]]\n\n==Home media==\nA region 1 DVD of the film was released on March 12, 2002.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0229003|title=New Port South}}\n* {{Mojo title|newportsouth}}\n* {{rotten-tomatoes|new_port_south}}\n\n[[Category:2001 films]]\n[[Category:2000s drama films]]\n[[Category:American drama films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Touchstone Pictures films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Films produced by John Hughes (filmmaker)]]\n", "name_user": "Moe1810", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Port_South"}
